diagram.name: Mouse Droid
description:
This document shows a system architecture
and software architecture for a mouse droid.
This is a small repair droid similar to the MSE-6 used on death star 1.

The document follows the arc42.org template
proposed by Gernot Starke and Peter Hruschka,

classifier.name: Introduction
description:
The mouse droid is a repair droid.
When programmed,
it autonomously drives to the destination location,
selects spare parts and tools
and exchanges damaged parts.

It is easily reprogrammable and can therefore also be used for
- cleaning tasks
- spying and surveillance tasks
- message delivery

classifier.name: Commander
description: The commander instructs the MoD5G on the mission to perform.

classifier.name: Repairability
description: The MoD5 hardware parts shall be exchangeable
in case they are damaged.

classifier.name: 30 years spare-parts supply
description:
The mechanical and electrical/electronics parts of the MoD5
shall be produceable in identical or similar form
and quality for 30 years after production of the unit.

classifier.name: Analyzability
description: The MoD5G shall allow to analyze faults
that occurred during operation.

classifier.name: Self-Diagnosis
description:
At the maintenance booth, 
the MoD5G shall provide an error log.
This error log contains detected errors from operation
and related environment conditions.
It also lists possible causes(faults).

classifier.name: Motor defect
description:
pre-condition:
- the MoD5G is performing a 1-day mission autonomously

trigger:
- a motor fails to operate
- the goals of the 1-day mission cannot be accomplished anymore

scenario:
- the MoD5G cancels the mission and returns to the service point
- a service mechanic reads out the error log
- the MoD5G proposes to replace the suspicious motor
- the service mechanic replaces the motor

classifier.name: Spare Parts Supply
description:
pre-condition:
- the stock of MoD5G spare parts is empty

trigger:
- 20 years after production, 
  a MoD5G needs a spare part that is not available anymore

scenario:
- a service mechanic orders a batch of parts
- a factory creates the parts that fit in form and quality to the MoD5G
- spare parts are delivered

classifier.name: Power Modes
description: refers to D0020#name

classifier.name: Health States
description: refers to D0021#name

classifier.name: Self-Preservation
description: In case a wookiee growls at the MoD5G,
it shall flee for self-preservation

classifier.name: Development and Production Context
description: This boundary encompasses the topics that are in scope during development and production.

classifier.name: Operational Context
description: This boundary encompasses the topics that are in scope during operation and maintenance.

classifier.name: Motor Type
description:
All motors are electrical step motors.

Step motors can be controlled
to move a defined number of steps
forward or backwards.

Note that that there are conditions
when the actual number of steps
is not equal to the previously requested 
number of steps, e.g. when accellerating
or slowing down too fast.

classifier.name: 2 of 3 Voter
description:
In order to support integrity of the system, the logic boards and the data storages are deployed three times as three identical parts.

All three parts shall produce the same outcomes given the same input.

If one deviates, it's result is ignored and the part is rebooted.

classifier.name: Cosmic Rays Information
description: When a cosmic ray interferes with the system,
the logic or the processed data gets corrupted.

classifier.name: Watchdog Supervision
description:
In order to support integrity of the logic and data,
a multi-stage hierarchy supervision shall be implemented.

Software watchdogs shall supervise the running software parts
in a way that logic errors and corrupted data can be detected.

A hardware watchdog shall supervise the software watchdogs.

In case of a failure in the supervised logic/data, the system shall reboot.
In case of a failure in the monitors, the system may reboot
or it shall fall back to a valid supervision mode.

classifier.name: Decision: Watchdog
description:
Arguments:

- The 2 of 3 voter is easier to implement but causes higher hardware costs.
- The watchdog supervision requires higher engineering efforts but is cheaper in production.

The watchdog supervision shall be implemented.

classifier.name: Maintenance booth
description:
A room in a star ship or on a planet
where the following tasks are performed:
- check operability of droids
- oil refill service
- repair of droids
- disintegration of old droids

classifier.name: Limp home mode may fail
description:
In case of a single fault, the MoD5G shall return
to the charging station.

The current design does not address the cases:
- the base logic board is damaged
- the energy cell is damaged
- the movement/steering motors are defect

classifier.name: Tactics Calculator
description: Calculate tactics based on given strategy and current situation model

classifier.name: Situation Model
description: The situation model refers to the (limited) knowledge of the software on environment and status.

classifier.name: Environment Model
description: The enironment model refers to the (limited) knowledge of the software on the real environment.

classifier.name: Status Model
description: The status model refers to the (limited) knowledge of the software on the real status.

classifier.name: Real Situation
description: The real situation refers to the reality of system status and environment.

classifier.name: Real Environment
description: The real environment refers to the physical environment of the system.

classifier.name: Real Status
description: The real status refers to the real system status. This may differ from what the sensors report.

classifier.name: Guiding Main Principles
description:
The functions of the MoD5G are divided
onto two logic boards.

The base logic
gets local sensor information
and controls things
within the system boundary of the MoD5G.

The main logic
gets sensor data of the environment
and calculates movement actions
to efficiently fulfill the mission
(that was programmed before).

classifier.name: Base Software Structure
description:
The software is basically structured into three parts:
- environment model generation
- calculating actions
- controlling execution of actions

classifier.name: Interoperability
description:
The programming and charging interfaces
of the MoD5G shall be compatible  to
- old republic terminals
- imperial terminals

classifier.name: Old Republic Programming IF
description:
The old republic protocol
for programming a droid
shall be supported.

classifier.name: Imperial Programming IF
description:
The imperial protocol
for programming a droid
shall be supported.

classifier.name: Universial Charging IF
description: The intergalactic standard protocol for power charging
shall be supported.

classifier.name: Fault Detection (main logic)
description:
Logic and data is supervised
by the SW Watchdog
located on the Base Micro Controller.

Every software component
on the Main Logic Board
shall check processed data
and report its health to the SW Watchdog
as well as passed checkpoints in the logic.

classifier.name: Fault Detection (base logic)
description:
The hardware of the Base Micro Controller
enables logic and data supervision.
Therefore no extra software solution
is implemented to monitor the base logic.

classifier.name: Fault Detection Strategy may fail
description:
The fault detection strategy for 
logic and data on the Main Logic Board
allows for unnoticed faults:

Not every error in logic can be detected
by checkpoints only.

classifier.name: Wookiee Detection
description:
Challenge: Detect presense of a Wookiee

Alt-1: Detect a growling wookie only by
analyzing the audio spectrum 
recorded from the microphone.
- pro: simple to implement
- con: may produce false alarms

Alt-2: Combine the Video and the Audio
sensor data to better distinguish
a growling wookie from a shouting officer.
- pro: better recognize wookiees
- con: dependency on video processing

Decision: Alt-1

Rationale: Reacting on a false alarm
is not mission-critical.

classifier.name: Risk: MoD5G does not drive back to terminal
description: - cause/fault: the base logic board is damaged
- risk/failure: the MoD5G cannot drive anymore

classifier.name: Risk: Wrong tactic is calculated
description:
- cause/fault: Due to cosmic rays, 
  the main logic board performs a miscalculation
  that goes unnoticed by control flow supervision
- risk/failure: the MoD5G calculates a tactic that
  results in falling off a cliff

classifier.name: health::all
description: The statemachine of all health states

classifier.name: power::all
description: The statemachine of all power states

classifier.name: Scope
description:
This document describes
system and software architecture for
engineering generation 5 of the mouse droid,
denoted by the term MoD5G.

classifier.name: Persist List
description:
the action list
shall be persisted,
so that
after a sudden reboot,
the next actions are 
immediately available.

classifier.name: Base location
description: The location where the MoD5G droid returns to when its mission is finished.
This location can be re-programmed.

classifier.name: Environmental Constraints
description: This package lists technical/physical constraints imposed by the environment in which to operate.

classifier.name: Mixed standards of terminals
description:
precondition:
- The MoD5G operates in an environment
  providing mixed terminal standards

trigger:
- The MoD5G drives to a charging or programming terminal
  which complied to either old republic or imperial standard.

scenario:
- The MoD5G determines the applicable standard
- The MoD5G uses the terminal for programming or charging

classifier.name: Cosmic Rays
description:
The droid shall ensure data and program integrity
and continue operation 
after cosmic rays may have interfered with normal operation.

Corrupted data must not be stored permanently.

classifier.name: Operating Temperatures
description: The droid shall be fully functional in the range 240K..360K,
it shall survive temperatures from 200K to 400K.

classifier.name: Mouse Droid (MoD5G)
description: The Mouse Droid (MoD5G) is a repair droid that can be instructed to perform a mission and which then autonomously selects tactics to achieve the mission goals.

classifier.name: Perform a 1-day Mission
description:
The mouse droid is able to perform a mission that takes several hours. The energy resources of the MoD5G last for up to one day.

- The commander programs a mission
- The mouse droid drives to the first location
- The mouse droid uses tools to remove a defective part
- The mouse droid installes a spare part
- Above steps are repeated for other goals
- The mouse droid returns to its base location (see D0013#name)

classifier.name: Drive to Location
description:
The mouse droid can explore its environment and calculate a route from the current ot the target location.

- The mouse droid explores its environment
- The mouse droid enriches internally memorized map
- The mouse droid calculates a route
- The mouse droid drives along the calculated route
- The mouse droid re-caclulates the route in case of new environment data
- The mouse droid reaches the target location

classifier.name: Use Tools
description:
The mouse droid has a couple of tools inside its chassis.

- The mouse droid uses a screw diver to untighten damaged parts
- The mouse droid uses a gripper to move the damaged part out of the way
- The mouse droid uses a gripper to put a spare part from its internal cargo bin to the target place
- The mouse droid uses a screw diver to tighten replaced parts
- The mouse droid uses a gripper to move the damaged part into its internal cargo bin.

(see D0014#name)

classifier.name: power::full_operation
description: While the MoD5G is in full_operation state, all software parts are running and able to react on input data.

classifier.name: health::limp_home
description: In case the full operation is not possible anymore, the MoD5G shall drive back to the home charging station.

classifier.name: Fan
description: A fan prevents overheating in hot environment conditions.

classifier.name: Main Logic Board
description: The main logic board consists of several electronic parts shown in D0022#name.

classifier.name: Base Logic Board
description: The base logic board consists of several electronic parts shown in D0035#name.

classifier.name: PMIC
description: Power Management Integrated Circuit

classifier.name: Base Micro Controller
description:
The base micro controller consists of
- logic unit
- data storage
- persistent data+logic storage
- self supervision (by ECC and lockstep-cores)
- HW watchdog
- clock
- temperature sensor
- io ports

classifier.name: Gripper
description: A tool that allows to grab objects and move them.

classifier.name: Tool-Window (2)
description: A tool window is a flap in the chassis that protects screw driver, gripper and cargo bin when unused.

classifier.name: Motivator
description: A motivator is a basic component needed to keep going on.

classifier.name: Explore Environment
description: When the mouse droid is missing relevant data on the environment, it plans a list of actions that suits the purpose of gaining the missing knowledge.

classifier.name: Plan tasks
description: The mouse droid creates a list of actions to fulfill the given mission.
If data on the environment is missing, it plans an explortion task and re-plans the action list later.

classifier.name: Outer World
description:
The main logic
addresses the following tasks:
- calculating movement actions
  to be performed by base logic (tactics)
- evaluating sensor signals
  from microphone and camera

classifier.name: Motor Controller
description: Move motors according to calculated tactics

classifier.name: Inner World
description:
The base logic
addresses the following tasks:
- charging
- programming
- steering the motors
- self-check

classifier.name: SW Watchdog
description:
The SW Watchdog shall check

- validity of data as well as
- validity of sequence of checkpoints

received from software components
on the Main Logic Board.

See also D0030#name.

classifier.name: Electrical Parts and Electronics
description:
The main components of the electric parts are
- a set of cables and connectors
- a set of sensors and actuators,
- the energy cell and
- two printed circuit boards (PCB) containing the electronic parts.
